{"questionId":"7677","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>The spacetime diagram shows the axes of an inertial reference frame S and the axes of a&nbsp;second inertial reference frame S′ that moves relative to S with speed 0.745<em>c</em>. When clocks&nbsp;in both frames show zero the origins of the two frames coincide.</p>\n<p><img src=\"__IMG__/336c9570bb6a44dc13f5034595b672ab2f612c6c.png\"></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>Event E has coordinates <em>x</em> = 1 m and <em>ct</em> = 0 in frame S. Show that in frame S′ the space&nbsp;coordinate and time coordinate of event E are</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p><em>ct</em>′ = –1.1 m.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><em>t</em>′ = «<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\gamma \\left( {t - \\frac{{vx}}{{{c^2}}}} \\right)\">\n  <mi>γ</mi>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mrow>\n      <mi>t</mi>\n      <mo>−</mo>\n      <mfrac>\n        <mrow>\n          <mi>v</mi>\n          <mi>x</mi>\n        </mrow>\n        <mrow>\n          <mrow>\n            <msup>\n              <mi>c</mi>\n              <mn>2</mn>\n            </msup>\n          </mrow>\n        </mrow>\n      </mfrac>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span> =»&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"1.499 \\times \\left( {0 - \\frac{{0.745c \\times 1}}{{{c^2}}}} \\right)\">\n  <mn>1.499</mn>\n  <mo>×</mo>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>0</mn>\n      <mo>−</mo>\n      <mfrac>\n        <mrow>\n          <mn>0.745</mn>\n          <mi>c</mi>\n          <mo>×</mo>\n          <mn>1</mn>\n        </mrow>\n        <mrow>\n          <mrow>\n            <msup>\n              <mi>c</mi>\n              <mn>2</mn>\n            </msup>\n          </mrow>\n        </mrow>\n      </mfrac>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span> «= <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\" - \\frac{{1.11}}{c}\">\n  <mo>−</mo>\n  <mfrac>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>1.11</mn>\n    </mrow>\n    <mi>c</mi>\n  </mfrac>\n</math></span>»</p>\n<p>«<em>ct</em>′ = –1.1 m»</p>\n<p><em><strong>OR</strong></em></p>\n<p>using spacetime interval 0 − 1<sup>2</sup> = (<em>ct</em>′)<sup>2</sup>&nbsp;− 1.5<sup>2</sup>&nbsp;⇒ «<em>ct</em>′ = –1.1» ✔</p>","meta":{"questionId":"7677","referenceCode":"18N.3.SL.TZ0.5a.ii","subjectId":"46-dp-physics-last-assessment-2024","title":"ct′ = –1.1 m.","paper":"3","level":"SL","questionNumber":"a.ii","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 1]","breadcrumbLabels":["Option A: Relativity","Option A: Relativity","Option A: Relativity (Core topics)","A.2 – Lorentz transformations","Option A: Relativity","Option A: Relativity (Core topics)"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}